{"id": "EUVD-2023-60279", "enisaUuid": "d6f5f60f-75d0-3a50-a05b-0c84a8a5ef85", "description": "In the Linux kernel, the following vulnerability has been resolved:\n\ndrm/rockchip: dw_hdmi: cleanup drm encoder during unbind\n\nThis fixes a use-after-free crash during rmmod.\n\nThe DRM encoder is embedded inside the larger rockchip_hdmi,\nwhich is allocated with the component. The component memory\ngets freed before the main drm device is destroyed. Fix it\nby running encoder cleanup before tearing down its container.\n\n[moved encoder cleanup above clk_disable, similar to bind-error-path]", "datePublished": "2025-12-24T12:22:58", "dateUpdated": "2026-01-05T10:33:34", "baseScore": 0.0, "references": ["https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/110d4202522373d629d14597af9bac97eb58bd67", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/218fe9b624545f4bcfb16cdb35ac3d60c8b0d8c7", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/b5af48eedcb53491c02ded55d5991e03d6da6dbf", "https://nvd.nist.gov/vuln/detail/CVE-2023-54047"], "aliases": ["CVE-2023-54047"], "assigner": "Linux", "epss": 0.02, "enisaIdProduct": [{"id": "132ba5e5-683f-3814-b0e6-60283ce5529c", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "8e3b16e2117409625b89807de3912ff773aea354 <110d4202522373d629d14597af9bac97eb58bd67"}, {"id": "339c0b8d-2a37-3dc0-8013-007719faea3e", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "8e3b16e2117409625b89807de3912ff773aea354 <218fe9b624545f4bcfb16cdb35ac3d60c8b0d8c7"}, {"id": "74b6840c-9265-3dcb-8294-c386cf857113", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 6.3.4"}, {"id": "865ef2b1-2482-3d20-b2d3-937f4bb8608d", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 0"}, {"id": "88d33cf1-f02f-30c7-a3ec-d754a6b1d646", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "1da177e4c3f41524e886b7f1b8a0c1fc7321cac2 <218fe9b624545f4bcfb16cdb35ac3d60c8b0d8c7"}, {"id": "8b064d8c-15a5-31d2-a238-00267fb40c14", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "1da177e4c3f41524e886b7f1b8a0c1fc7321cac2 <b5af48eedcb53491c